title: Ask HN: Should AI generated content come with a disclosure label?
text: With the progression in AI generated content, it is becoming increasingly difficult to tell the difference between human and computer generated. Should content have to be labeled as AI generated? Should there be regulation to enforce this?

Ask HN: How to switch to a different programming language?
text:
I've been working using the same programming language professionally for the better part of about 10 years. It's been an easy transition between the few jobs that I have had.

Lately, I feel like it's time for to move away from this language as I've really started to hate its, at least what I now believe to be, frustrating shortcomings.

What's throwing me off is that most titles require senior developers to have at least n number of years of experience with their stack and even frameworks.

I have been working on side-projects in the language I would like to switch to, but nothing that I feel confident enough to publish anywhere yet.

So, my question. How have you pulled off switching between different languages, both as obtaining the requisite skills (conventions, tool chains, libraries) on your own and actually making the switch?

text:

Ask HN: What's on your Christmas wish list?
text:
I am struggling with coming up with wishes for this year, so I thought: Surely there's a thread full of great ideas on hackernews.

Unfortunately I wasn't able to find one.

I'm sure there's a gold mine of knowledge regarding interesting gadgets, games, books etc. in this great community, so lets help each other:

What are your wishes - that good hackers would find interesting - for this year?

(Feel free to mention things that you already have, but would be great as gifts)
